			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Great use for /bandolier<a name="73404"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 05 11:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, when I'm tanking I twist all 4 dots to hold aggro.  It would be way too much effort to sway in the drum when each dot landed.  So I don't, cos I'm lazy...  Then along comes bandolier and I get to thinking!
<br />

<br />
ok, set bandolier 0 to equip drum and set bandolier 1 to equip your tankin weapons (bandoliers are number 0-3 not 1-4)
<br />

<br />
Create 4 hotkeys for each of your DoTs
<br />

<br />
<b>/bandolier activate 1</b> (load weapons)
<br />
<b>/stopsong</b>
<br />
<b>/pause 20, /cast x</b>
<br />
<b>/bandolier activate 0</b> (load drum)
<br />

<br />
So what does that do? 
<br />

<br />
When you start to cast it makes sure you have weapons in your hands, and then casts the dot.  Just before the DoT lands it loads your drum.   Then when you hit your NEXT dot, your weapons are reloaded.
<br />

<br />
Upside: Many, its just so goddammed easy to swap in the drums.  I estimate this has upped my DPS by 30% when melee soloing or tanking and with appropriate improvement in aggro.
<br />

<br />
Downside: Only one really so far, and that is when you are bashed and the song is interrupted . You have to bash the key a couple of times to interrupt the macro. Also theres a bit of bandolier spam.
<br />

<br />
For me this totally rocks, up to you whether the downside outweighs the upside. But personally I think this is teh win for tanking and melee soloing!  
<br />

<br />
For the other songs I make sure I activate the weapon bandolier. So I have a full set of hotkeys for when I am in tankmode.  No big deal, a few mins of typing and it works a charm.  Maybe i will make a mana song key to swap in lute... who knows.
<br />

<br />
Cheers
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
